# Cursor AI Rules — codecontext

## Project
Go CLI tool that indexes source code into a SQLite-backed code graph. Exposes via MCP, web UI, and AI analysis. Parses Go, Python, JS/TS, Java.

## Build & Test
- Build: `go build -o codecontext`
- Test all: `go test ./...`
- Test parsers: `go test ./pkg/parser/ -v`
- Lint: `go vet ./...`
- Smoke test: `./codecontext index . && ./codecontext stats`

## Architecture
- `main.go` — CLI entry point, command routing
- `pkg/db/` — GORM + SQLite (models.go for schema, db.go for operations)
- `pkg/parser/` — Language router; sub-packages: `go/`, `python/`, `javascript/`, `java/`
- `pkg/parser/go/` — Uses stdlib `go/ast`
- `pkg/parser/{python,javascript,java}/` — Uses tree-sitter (`github.com/smacker/go-tree-sitter`)
- `pkg/indexer/` — Parallel file indexer with worker pool, mutex-serialized DB writes
- `pkg/mcp/` — MCP server using official Go SDK (`github.com/modelcontextprotocol/go-sdk/mcp`)
- `pkg/web/` — Self-contained SPA (HTML/CSS/JS embedded as Go string constant)
- `pkg/llm/` — LLM provider abstraction (Ollama, Azure, OpenAI)
- `pkg/ai/` — AI analysis chains

## Code Style
- Go 1.24+, stdlib `testing` only (no testify etc.)
- Error handling: `fmt.Errorf("context: %w", err)`
- Logging: `log/slog` JSON handler to stderr (MCP), `fmt.Printf` for CLI
- Commit style: `type(scope): message`
- No unnecessary abstractions — keep it simple

## Key Patterns
- Tree-sitter parsers: `sitter.NewParser()` → set language → `parser.ParseCtx()` → walk AST via `node.NamedChild(i)`
- MCP tools registered via `mcpsdk.AddTool()` with typed input structs using `json`/`jsonschema` tags
- DB: GORM auto-migration, `FirstOrCreate` to prevent duplicates, `WithTx()` for transactions
- Indexer: MD5 hash change detection, respects `.gitignore`

## When Editing
- Parser changes → run `go test ./pkg/parser/ -v`
- Any change → run `go test ./...`
- New parser language → see CLAUDE.md "Adding a new parser language"
- New MCP tool → see CLAUDE.md "Adding a new MCP tool"
- Web UI edits → modify the string constant in `pkg/web/ui.go`
